cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AR 

The paper focuses on automatic performance debugging of parallel programs, which involves analyzing performance metrics and uncovering root causes of performance bottlenecks. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper proposes a set of simple performance metrics and algorithms for clustering and searching, which could also be relevant to Performance Analysis (cs.PF) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The implementation of the AutoAnalyzer system involves programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and potentially also Architecture (cs.AR) if hardware considerations are taken into account.
